Vice President Mike Pence spoke with a radio station about the aftermath of Hurricane Harvey and the federal government's response. He expressed gratitude for the support and timely information provided by the station and praised the resilience of the people of southeast Texas. Pence assured listeners that the federal government is committed to providing resources for rescue and recovery efforts. He urged people to listen to local officials and emphasized that help is on the way. Pence also addressed concerns about the allocation of resources and assured that funding will be available for those affected by the hurricane. He thanked the radio station for its commitment to the community.